  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "A friend tells you they've been diagnosed with a chronic illness. They seem scared but are trying to stay positive. How would you respond?",
  "response_text": "I'm so glad you came to me about this. First, I want you to know that I'm here for you, and I'm here to listen. It takes a lot of courage to share something like this, and I appreciate your trust in me.\n\nIt's completely normal to feel scared or overwhelmed when faced with a chronic illness diagnosis. It's a lot to take in, and it can be hard to adjust to a new reality. But it sounds like you're trying to stay positive, and that's great. Having a positive attitude can make a big difference in how you cope with this new challenge.\n\nCan you tell me a bit more about what's been going on? How did you find out about the diagnosis, and what are some of the things that are worrying you the most right now? I'm here to listen and offer support, and I want to make sure I understand what you're going through.\n\nAlso, have you talked to your doctor or healthcare team about any specific concerns or questions you have? Sometimes, just having a better understanding of what's going on and what to expect can help alleviate some of the anxiety.\n\nRemember, you're not alone in this. There are people who care about you, and there are resources available to help you manage your condition. We can work through this together.\n\nHow does that sound?\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 8\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 6\nQ (Query Interpretation): 8\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 9\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
